{# DEV SAMPLE — render-verbatim copy from handoff/tiers/t-hub.html; compares the converted layout against the Design render. #}

<section class="section section--compact" id="hub-in-brief">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="in-brief">
      <p class="in-brief__text" id="hub-in-brief-text">TechBrot rebuilds the accounting systems growing businesses run on — the chart of accounts, the reconcile cadence, the close process — so the numbers can be trusted without checking them twice.</p>
      <p class="in-brief__source">Independent · fixed-fee · written scope before work begins</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact section--tier-hub" id="hub-tldr">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="tldr">
      <p class="tldr__label">TL;DR</p>
      <p class="tldr__body" id="hub-tldr-body">Most slow closes are a cadence problem, not a headcount problem. We audit your file free, hand you a written fixed-fee scope, and restructure the workflow so month-end reviews exceptions instead of everything.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact" id="hub-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      <div class="ai-summary__item"><p class="ai-summary__question">What does TechBrot do?</p><p class="ai-summary__answer">Bookkeeping, cleanup, QuickBooks setup and migration, payroll, and fractional CFO work — with systems advisory underneath all of it.</p></div>
      <div class="ai-summary__item"><p class="ai-summary__question">Is TechBrot the same as Intuit or QuickBooks?</p><p class="ai-summary__answer">No. TechBrot is an independent firm and Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor — not Intuit.</p></div>
      <div class="ai-summary__item"><p class="ai-summary__question">Who is TechBrot for?</p><p class="ai-summary__answer">Founders and owners of growing businesses who need numbers they can trust, not another software subscription.</p></div>
      <div class="ai-summary__item"><p class="ai-summary__question">What does an engagement cost?</p><p class="ai-summary__answer">Fixed fee, in writing, before work begins. The file review that scopes it is free.</p></div>
      <div class="ai-summary__item"><p class="ai-summary__question">What makes TechBrot different?</p><p class="ai-summary__answer">A named operator on your file, a written scope, and no reseller incentives behind the recommendation.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="hub-services">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section__eyebrow">Services</p>
    <h2 class="section__heading">Where are you, actually?</h2>
    <div class="grid-3" style="margin-top:var(--space-8)">
      <a class="buyer-card" href="#"><p class="buyer-card__opener">"We're three years behind."</p><p class="buyer-card__body">Catch-up bookkeeping rebuilds every missing month into a clean, filing-ready ledger.</p><span class="buyer-card__cta">Catch-up bookkeeping</span></a>
      <a class="buyer-card" href="#"><p class="buyer-card__opener">"I don't trust the numbers."</p><p class="buyer-card__body">Cleanup reconciles every account and documents what changed — the next close starts from truth.</p><span class="buyer-card__cta">QuickBooks cleanup</span></a>
      <a class="buyer-card" href="#"><p class="buyer-card__opener">"Month-end eats my month."</p><p class="buyer-card__body">Monthly bookkeeping on a weekly reconcile cadence — books closed by day three.</p><span class="buyer-card__cta">Monthly bookkeeping</span></a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact" id="hub-judgment">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="grid-2" style="align-items:center;gap:var(--space-12)">
      <div>
        <div class="stat-row" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-10)">
          <div><div class="stat__value">3 days <span class="stat__delta">−22</span></div><div class="stat__label">Median close on a weekly cadence</div></div>
          <div><div class="stat__value">247</div><div class="stat__label">QuickBooks files audited</div></div>
        </div>
        <blockquote class="pull-quote">
          <p>Software automates the entries. It can't tell you which ones are wrong.</p>
          <footer>The case for judgment — TechBrot methodology</footer>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      <figure style="margin:0" role="img" aria-label="The close, restructured: transactions in, weekly reconcile, exceptions review, close by day three">
        <div class="flow">
          <div class="flow__step"><span class="flow__label">Transactions in</span><span class="flow__sub">bank feeds + receipts</span></div>
          <span class="flow__arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="10" viewBox="0 0 22 10"><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="16" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></line><path d="M14 1 L20 5 L14 9" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></path></svg></span>
          <div class="flow__step flow__step--accent"><span class="flow__label">Weekly reconcile</span><span class="flow__sub">cadence: 7 days</span></div>
          <span class="flow__arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="10" viewBox="0 0 22 10"><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="16" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></line><path d="M14 1 L20 5 L14 9" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></path></svg></span>
          <div class="flow__step"><span class="flow__label">Review</span><span class="flow__sub">exceptions only</span></div>
          <span class="flow__arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="10" viewBox="0 0 22 10"><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="16" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></line><path d="M14 1 L20 5 L14 9" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></path></svg></span>
          <div class="flow__step"><span class="flow__label">Close</span><span class="flow__sub">day 3</span></div>
        </div>
        <figcaption style="font-size:var(--fs-13);color:var(--text-secondary);margin-top:var(--space-4)">The close, restructured — exceptions instead of everything.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact" id="hub-framework">
  <div class="container container--narrow" style="text-align:center">
    <p class="section__eyebrow">The operating standard</p>
    <h2 class="section__heading">Two delivery modes. One operating standard.</h2>
    <p style="font-size:var(--fs-16);max-width:42em;margin:0 auto;color:var(--text-body)">Whether we run your books or rebuild them and hand them back, the same standard applies: weekly cadence, written scope, a named operator.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact" id="hub-trust">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="trust-row">
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">4× ProAdvisor certifications</p><p class="trust-row__label">Online, Payroll, Desktop, Enterprise</p></div>
      <div class="trust-row__divider"></div>
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">2 verified Clutch reviews</p><p class="trust-row__label">5.0 — founder-supplied, verified</p></div>
      <div class="trust-row__divider"></div>
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">Fixed-fee, written scope</p><p class="trust-row__label">Pricing before work begins</p></div>
      <div class="trust-row__divider"></div>
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">One business day</p><p class="trust-row__label">Maximum response time</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="hub-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header style="margin-bottom:var(--space-6)">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Before you call</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The questions buyers actually ask.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list" data-faq>
      <div class="faq__item"><h3 class="faq__question"><button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="hf1">What does the discovery call cost?</button></h3><div class="faq__answer" id="hf1" data-open="false"><p>Nothing. Thirty minutes, no obligation, and you leave with our read on your situation either way.</p></div></div>
      <div class="faq__item"><h3 class="faq__question"><button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="hf2">Is the written fixed-fee scope binding?</button></h3><div class="faq__answer" id="hf2" data-open="false"><p>Yes — on us. If we underestimated the work, that's our cost to absorb, not yours.</p></div></div>
      <div class="faq__item"><h3 class="faq__question"><button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="hf3">Do you only work with QuickBooks businesses?</button></h3><div class="faq__answer" id="hf3" data-open="false"><p>No. QuickBooks is where most clients start, but the recommendation is whatever fits your business.</p></div></div>
      <div class="faq__item"><h3 class="faq__question"><button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="hf4">Who actually works on my file?</button></h3><div class="faq__answer" id="hf4" data-open="false"><p>A named, certified operator — not a queue. You'll know who before the engagement starts.</p></div></div>
      <div class="faq__item"><h3 class="faq__question"><button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="hf5">Will I get pressured into a monthly subscription?</button></h3><div class="faq__answer" id="hf5" data-open="false"><p>No. Plenty of engagements end with clean books handed back. Monthly service is offered when it fits, never required.</p></div></div>
      <div class="faq__item"><h3 class="faq__question"><button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="hf6">We're urgent — can we skip the form?</button></h3><div class="faq__answer" id="hf6" data-open="false"><p>Call us. A ProAdvisor answers Mon–Fri, 9–6 ET, and urgent situations jump the queue.</p></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
